## How Wyatt works
- Directs Cursor via prompts, does not hand-edit code
- Commits frequently, reverts over debugging broken state
- Pushback > validation; start new agents if Cursor spirals on the same code
- Screenshots for visual review mid-session
- Production verification rule: post-push, fetch production main.js and `Select-String` for the new code. Local grep alone has produced false positives.
- PowerShell env: `Select-String` not `grep`; single-line commit messages with `-m "..."`.
- Diff-before-apply is a hard rule. Unified diff format, wait for ack, then apply.
- **NEW DEPLOY RULE**: Use `npm run ship` (git push && npx partykit deploy) for every session update to keep protocol in sync. GitHub main does not match deployed edge. PartyKit DO state persists across deploys. Deploys do not reset in-memory server state.
- **`room.getConnections()` returns an Iterator, not an Array.** Do not call `.map().join()` or Array methods on it. Use `for...of` or spread explicitly (`[...room.getConnections()]`). A single bad `.join()` took down production for ~90 seconds in Session 13.
- **Behavior-changing diffs require human playtest on prod** before moving to the next diff. String checks confirm code shipped; they do not confirm behavior
